This paper discusses the design of recommender systems, which is a topic that falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. The paper also touches on the potential negative consequences of RS, such as filter bubbles and user homogenization, which are relevant to the social and information science (cs.SI) and cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a theoretical model for RS design, which could be considered a machine learning (cs.LG) approach.
